You write a new note on the same file...

AFTER:   notes tree:  abc123 -> note222    (was -> note111)
```

The old note blob `note111` still exists in the object store. The previous commit on `refs/notes/mycelium` still points to the old tree where `abc123 -> note111`. So `git log -p refs/notes/mycelium` shows the full history.

