Option A (parallel meta ref) is the right long-term architecture if you need truly opaque content (PNG, protobuf, compiled artifacts). It maps naturally to the existing slot mechanism (`--slot meta` could be the metadata channel). But it doubles operational complexity and should only be adopted when there is a real use case for non-text notes.

